         <abstract>
            <p>The new tax law is perhaps the most comprehensive since the enactment of the revised Internal Revenue Code of 1954. Longstanding tax provisions have been modified or eliminated in the interest of achieving equity among taxpayers. On the other hand, corporate financial plans and individual investor decisions affected by tax considerations may require substantial alteration.</p>
